bug.short_desc: Preferences -> PHP Executables throws up error..

long_desc.thetext:
Build ID: M20071023-1652
Steps To Reproduce: 1.Edit -> Preferences -> PHP -> PHP Exceutables 2.Error: The currently displayed page contains invalid values. 3.
More information:

I think these are actually two problems:
1) PHP executables cannot be maintained. 2) When going to the page, e.g. also Edit -> Preferences -> PHP -> Debug, the "The currently displayed page contains invalid values" error is thrown yet the page is not even activated in the UI. This leeds to confusion for the user.
Bottom line: currently PHP debugging cannot be configured- which makes PDT pretty useless for me. Suggesting to increase severity.
Any chance this is going to get fixed? Thanks!
Verified this is still an issue in the current 2.0 nightlies.
Fixed for me by deleting all *pdt* preferences files from the workspace\.metadata\.plugins\org.eclipse.core.runtime\.settings directory. I believe this could be closed.

(In reply to comment #5) > Fixed for me by deleting all *pdt* preferences files from the > workspace\.metadata\.plugins\org.eclipse.core.runtime\.settings directory. I > believe this could be closed.
I did not want to lose all my prefs, so I dug deeper and fixed this by commenting(#) out the line
org.eclipse.php.debug.coreinstalledPHPLocations=C\:\\PHP
in $HOME/workspace/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.core.runtime/.settings/org.eclipse.php.debug.core.prefs
Presumably this was a leftover from copying the workspace created on Windows (there were a number of obsolete (non-PDT) prefs files in that directory as well).
HTH
PointedEars
